        " مِنْ شَقَاءِ الْعَيْشِ ضِيقُ الْمَنْزِلِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Ibrahim Bin Abu Al Balaad, from Ali Bin Abu Al Mugheira, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘From a miserable living, is a narrow home’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Abu Ali al-Ash‘ariy has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il from Ibrahim ibn abu al-Balad from Ali ibn abu al-Mughirah who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Of the misfortunes in the worldly life is a small and congested house.’” "
        ]
      }
